# ============================================
# K441 — librarian-mcp reproducibility carve-outs
# ============================================
# The internal librarian-mcp/ directory hosts source for the in-repo MCP
# server. Several of its critical files (package.json, tsconfig.json,
# package-lock.json, registry.yaml, SP*.md spec files, README) are caught
# by the broad *.json / *.yaml / *.md ignore rules above. Without these
# explicit negations, a fresh clone cannot `npm install` the librarian
# and the Cathedral cannot start. .ts source files under librarian-mcp/src/
# are not affected (no `*.ts` ignore rule exists in this file).
#
# DO NOT re-broaden these patterns without ALSO updating librarian-mcp/README.md
# (which documents the policy).
!librarian-mcp/package.json
!librarian-mcp/package-lock.json
!librarian-mcp/tsconfig.json
!librarian-mcp/README.md
!librarian-mcp/stitchpunks/scribes/registry.yaml
!librarian-mcp/stitchpunks/SP*.md
!librarian-mcp/stitchpunks/README.md
!librarian-mcp/r10_cross_vendor/README.md
!librarian-mcp/scrambler/README.md
!librarian-mcp/touchstone/README.md
# Index payloads and runtime state stay ignored — they are regenerable
# via `npm run rebuild` and would bloat git history. Force-adding them is
# explicitly NOT desired.
librarian-mcp/index/*.json
librarian-mcp/index/*.jsonl
librarian-mcp/stitchpunks/sp*_state.json

# ============================================
# B117 follow-up — Stitchpunk Corps Python source
# ============================================
# Same class of reproducibility fix as K441 Half B. The root `*.py` ignore
# rule catches runtime-critical Python source under librarian-mcp/stitchpunks/
# (SP-1 Cartographer, SP-5 Sentinel, SP-6 Scribe, SP-16 Recombiner, SP-18
# Prose Provenance, SP-20 Pollinator, session_start.py, session_end.py, etc.).
# Without these negations a fresh clone cannot run the Stitchpunk Corps.
# __pycache__/ and *.pyc stay ignored (generated).
!librarian-mcp/stitchpunks/*.py
!librarian-mcp/stitchpunks/**/*.py
librarian-mcp/stitchpunks/**/__pycache__/
librarian-mcp/stitchpunks/**/*.pyc

# ============================================
# K442 (B117) — TouchStone engine + predicates carve-out
# ============================================
# The root `*.py` / `*.json` ignore rules also catch runtime-critical files
# under librarian-mcp/touchstone/ (verify.py, ledger.py, predicates/*.py,
# manifest.json, manifest_schema.json, the migrate_letter_predicates.py
# tooling, and the tests/ subtree). Without these negations the K442
# 3-state Letter Predicate Ladder system cannot reach a fresh clone, and
# `python touchstone/verify.py --letters-summary` (called by brief_me) and
# `python touchstone/migrate_letter_predicates.py --apply` would silently
# fail. __pycache__/ and *.pyc stay ignored (generated).
!librarian-mcp/touchstone/*.py
!librarian-mcp/touchstone/**/*.py
!librarian-mcp/touchstone/manifest.json
!librarian-mcp/touchstone/manifest_schema.json
librarian-mcp/touchstone/**/__pycache__/
librarian-mcp/touchstone/**/*.pyc
# Append-only ledger stays ignored — runtime state, not source.
librarian-mcp/touchstone/ledger.jsonl
